d", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2018-08-09T21:58:58Z", "updated_at": "2020-11-12T02:38:31Z", "closed_at": "2020-11-12T02:38:30Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Moved from https://github.com/datalad/datalad/pull/2725\r\n\r\nwe need to provide some way to shorten path to the fields in the metadata. To access any metadata field you need `{metadata[extractor][FIELD]}` to get actual field.  Since we cannot use `.` as a separator, I thought that may be we could provide support for `/` (which shouldn't be anywhere in the keys, right?) with some glob or regex semantic.  E.g. so instead of\r\n\r\n`'{path}: {metadata[annex][participant_id]!r} {metadata[annex][sex]:>6} {metadata[annex][age]}'`\r\n\r\n(where `!` and `:` are just for an example) I could say\r\n\r\n'{path}: {annex/participant_id!r} {annex/sex:>6} {annex/age}'\r\n\r\nor even\r\n\r\n`'{path}: {*/participant_id!r} {*/sex:>6} {*/age}'`\r\n\r\nwith crash or join (`', '.join`) happening if multiple metadata records provide those fields.\r\nedit: may be `/` in the hierarchy should/could be used in the 'query' itself to stay consistent with the output formatting...?\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "yarikoptic", "id": 39889, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODg5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39889?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic", "html_url": "https://github.com/yarikoptic", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.c